Description: Setting up Kubernetes Context with AWS EKS

This provides the info to pair your AWS EKS Cluster witn your AWS
profile.  This information is all kept in a kubectl file:

  ~/.kube/config

Values needed for this command are:

  - AWS Region  - Where is the cluster located (i.e. us-east-2)
  - AWS Profile - Profile name used when setting up aws-credentials
  - K8S Cluster - Name and alias used to setup local context

  aws eks update-kubeconfig \
      --region {aws-region}} \
      --name {k8s-cluster} \
      --alias {k8s-cluster} \
      --profile {aws-profile}